<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0"/>
  <title>404 - The Door Is Gone</title>
  <style>
    @import url('https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=UnifrakturCook:wght@700&display=swap');

    body {
      margin: 0;
      padding: 3rem;
      background: #0a0a0a;
      color: #ccc;
      font-family: 'UnifrakturCook', cursive;
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      align-items: center;
      justify-content: center;
      height: 100vh;
      text-align: center;
      background: radial-gradient(ellipse at center, #111 0%, #000 100%);
      overflow: hidden;
      position: relative;
    }

    h1 {
      font-size: 4rem;
      color: #8b0000;
      text-shadow: 0 0 10px red;
      animation: flicker 1.8s infinite alternate;
    }

    p {
      font-size: 1.2rem;
      max-width: 700px;
      margin-top: 1rem;
      line-height: 1.6;
      animation: fadeIn 2s ease forwards;
    }

    .link-back {
      margin-top: 2rem;
      font-size: 1.1rem;
      color: #ff6666;
      text-decoration: none;
      border-bottom: 1px dashed #ff6666;
      transition: color 0.3s ease;
    }

    .link-back:hover {
      color: #fff;
      border-color: #fff;
    }

    @keyframes flicker {
      0% { opacity: 0.8; }
      50% { opacity: 0.4; text-shadow: 0 0 15px crimson; }
      100% { opacity: 1; }
    }

    @keyframes fadeIn {
      from { opacity: 0; transform: translateY(10px); }
      to { opacity: 1; transform: translateY(0); }
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <h1>The Door Is Gone</h1>
  <p>You're not where you're supposed to be.</p>
  <p>Maybe the link was broken. Maybe the path was buried. Maybe the door just... vanished.</p>
  <p>Whatever the reason, there's no page here. Only silence.</p>
  <a class="link-back" href="/">Go back while you still can.</a>
</body>
</html>
